The fruits should be harvested from 6 am to 9 am or 5 pm to 5 pm. At this time, the atmosphere is cold and the atmosphere complements the next cold weather. Use a steel scissor for fruit harvesting. Avoid iron scissors or knives. It is also convenient to use a small seater for this purpose. Remove the fruit from hand and avoid the use of pots and pears. Avoid using water while at the time of harvesting. Rinse should be washed with water or washed with a cloth at the time of appliance. 4 to 6 cm of removing the fruit Keep the stalk Usually the finger length should be with the fruit. Cut the stalk to the right hand by holding the left hand. Importantly, do not worry that there will be a slight flick if you do not have any scarcity in the crop, or if the crop that comes out of the nearby area is blighted. Cleanliness of the person taking fruit is also very important.
